cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the addition of a verifiability layer to an existing online voting system to ensure the integrity of the election. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper describes the use of distributed ledger technology to manage the verifiability data in a decentralised way for resilience and trust. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the societal implications of online voting and the need for trustworthy systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the Selene-based verifiability layer and the incremental changes towards fully trustworthy online voting systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on the development of new algorithms or data structures, but rather on the integration of an existing protocol into an online voting system.
